ðŸŽ¯The challenge: Write a function that finds the maximum length of any Roman numeral up to n;
ðŸ“ŒDetails: The first five Roman numerals are I, II, III, IV, V, and so the maximum length of any Roman numeral up to n=5 is 3;
ðŸ‘€What your function should do?
Write a function "MaxRomanLength' that takes a positive integer n as an input and outputs the maximum length of any Roman numeral up to n.
Use 'RomanNumeral' to generate the numerals;

-----SCRATCH AREA-----
In[28]:= RomanNumeral[Range[8]]
Out[28]= {"I", "II", "III", "IV", "V", "VI", "VII", "VIII"}

In[29]:= StringLength[%]
Out[29]= {1, 2, 3, 2, 1, 2, 3, 4}

In[30]:= Max[%]
Out[30]= 4

-----------------------

---------CODE----------

MaxRomanLength[n_Integer?Positive] := 
 Max@StringLength[RomanNumeral[Range[n]]]

